  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>RepairQ offers opportunity management for contacts (leads), customers, opportunities (quotes), and appointments. Users can easily create quotes that can be printed, emailed, and converted into tickets.</p><p>A quote has all of the features of a standard ticket with a couple of key differences:</p><ul><li><p>Inventory is not pulled nor consumed for a quote.</p></li><li><p>Quotes are not included in revenue reports.</p></li></ul><p>Quotes also use the same status system that you use for tickets and repairs. Converting a quote into an active ticket is a one-click process, and once converted, the related inventory is immediately pulled to the ticket.</p><h3 id=\"RepairQOpportunities(Quotes)-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1934458927\" rel=\"nofollow\">Contacts Overview</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/2022080562\" rel=\"nofollow\">Quotes: Save a Ticket as a Quote</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1934917634\" rel=\"nofollow\">Quotes: Convert a Quote to a Ticket</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934491696/Appointments\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934491696\" data-linked-resource-version=\"6\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Appointment Resources</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/1933246465\" rel=\"nofollow\">Automated Notification Resources</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933246809/image-20230622-175648.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"RepairQOpportunities(Quotes)-CustomerQuoteToolsinRepairQ\">Customer Quote Tools in RepairQ</h2><p>Users can locate Quote features by going to the Opportunities section of the Navigation Bar.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933246809/image-20230622-175651.png?api=v2\"></span><ul><li><p><strong>+ Contact</strong> - Create a new contact. This is a potential customer, i.e. lead, for your business. They are listed separately from your Customer list. They can be changed to a customer in their profile settings or by converting a quote they are assigned into a ticket.</p></li><li><p><strong>View Contacts</strong> - View your full list of contacts and customers. This list can also be sorted to show only leads.</p></li><li><p><strong>View Quotes</strong> - View a list of all quotes in your ticket queue.</p></li><li><p><strong>Appointments</strong> - Create and manage appointments for customers and leads.</p></li></ul><h2 id=\"RepairQOpportunities(Quotes)-IdentifyaQuoteinyourTicketQueue\">Identify a Quote in your Ticket Queue</h2><p>Quotes have an assigned number, just like a standard ticket. When searching your ticket queue, you can search for a ticket number or filter for <strong>Type: Quote</strong>. The Ticket Type (TT) indicator for a quote is a quotation mark symbol.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933246809/image-20230622-175653.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>When viewing a ticket, a quote is identified by the ticket type on the upper-left hand of the page.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933246809/image-20230622-175659.png?api=v2\"></span><hr/><h2 id=\"RepairQOpportunities(Quotes)-SaveaTicketasaQuote\">Save a Ticket as a Quote</h2><p>If you create a new ticket and would like to save it as a quote for your customer, you must have a customer and a repair device, item, or labor attached to the ticket. If the ticket meets these requirements, a new selection will appear at the bottom of the ticket, along with the standard ticket save statuses. Click <strong>Save as Quote</strong> to convert the ticket to a quote, which will be searchable in your Quote List and Ticket List (if filtered to include quotes).</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: This option will only be possible when saving the ticket for the first time. If it has already been progressed to an existing status, this option will not be available.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933246809/Quote%2010.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>START 1.22.X</p>",
